field.description: The last MsgSeqNum (34) value received by the FIX engine and processed by downstream application, such as trading engine or order routing system. Can be specified on every message sent. Useful for detecting a backlog with a counterparty.

field.name: RefTagID
field.description: The tag number of the FIX field being referenced.

field.name: RefMsgType
field.description: The MsgType (35) of the FIX message being referenced.

field.name: SessionRejectReason
field.description: Code to identify reason for a session-level Reject message.

field.name: BidRequestTransType
field.description: Identifies the Bid Request message type.

field.name: ContraBroker
field.description: Identifies contra broker. Standard NASD market-maker mnemonic is preferred.

field.name: ComplianceID
field.description: ID used to represent this transaction for compliance purposes (e.g. OATS reporting).

field.name: SolicitedFlag
field.description: Indicates whether or not the order was solicited.

field.name: ExecRestatementReason
field.description: Code to identify reason for an ExecutionRpt message sent with ExecType=Restated or used when communicating an unsolicited cancel.

field.name: BusinessRejectRefID
field.description: The value of the business-level "ID" field on the message being referenced.

field.name: BusinessRejectReason
field.description: Code to identify reason for a Business Message Reject message.

field.name: GrossTradeAmt
field.description: Total amount traded (e.g. CumQty (14) * AvgPx (6)) expressed in units of currency. For FX Futures this is used to express the notional value of a fill when LastQty and other quantity fields are express in terms of contract size.

field.name: NoContraBrokers
field.description: The number of ContraBroker (375) entries.

field.name: MaxMessageSize
field.description: Maximum number of bytes supported for a single message.

field.name: NoMsgTypes
field.description: Number of MsgTypes (35) in repeating group.

field.name: MsgDirection
field.description: Specifies the direction of the messsage.

field.name: NoTradingSessions
field.description: Number of TradingSessionIDs (336) in repeating group.

field.name: TotalVolumeTraded
field.description: Total volume (quantity) traded.

field.name: DiscretionInst
field.description: Code to identify the price a DiscretionOffsetValue (389) is related to and should be mathematically added to.

field.name: DiscretionOffsetValue
field.description: Amount (signed) added to the "related to" price specified via DiscretionInst (388), in the context of DiscretionOffsetType (842) (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was of type PriceOffset)

field.name: BidID
field.description: Unique identifier for Bid Response as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day.

field.name: ClientBidID
field.description: Unique identifier for a Bid Request as assigned by institution. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day.

field.name: ListName
field.description: Descriptive name for list order.

field.name: TotNoRelatedSym
field.description: Total number of securities. (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was named TotalNumSecurities)

field.name: BidType
field.description: Code to identify the type of Bid Request.

field.name: NumTickets
field.description: Total number of tickets.

field.name: SideValue1
field.description: Amounts in currency

field.name: SideValue2
field.description: Amounts in currency

field.name: NoBidDescriptors
field.description: Number of BidDescriptor (400) entries.

field.name: BidDescriptorType
field.description: Code to identify the type of BidDescriptor (400).

field.name: BidDescriptor
field.description: BidDescriptor value. Usage depends upon BidDescriptorTyp (399). If BidDescriptorType = 1 Industrials etc - Free text If BidDescriptorType = 2 "FR" etc - ISO Country Codes If BidDescriptorType = 3 FT00, FT250, STOX - Free text

field.name: SideValueInd
field.description: Code to identify which "SideValue" the value refers to. SideValue1 and SideValue2 are used as opposed to Buy or Sell so that the basket can be quoted either way as Buy or Sell.

field.name: LiquidityPctLow
field.description: Liquidity indicator or lower limit if TotalNumSecurities (393) > 1. Represented as a percentage.

field.name: LiquidityPctHigh
field.description: Upper liquidity indicator if TotalNumSecurities (393) > 1. Represented as a percentage.

field.name: LiquidityValue
field.description: Value between LiquidityPctLow (402) and LiquidityPctHigh (403) in Currency

field.name: EFPTrackingError
field.description: Eg Used in EFP trades 2% (EFP - Exchange for Physical ). Represented as a percentage.

field.name: FairValue
field.description: Used in EFP trades

field.name: OutsideIndexPct
field.description: Used in EFP trades. Represented as a percentage.

field.name: ValueOfFutures
field.description: Used in EFP trades

field.name: LiquidityIndType
field.description: Code to identify the type of liquidity indicator.

field.name: WtAverageLiquidity
field.description: Overall weighted average liquidity expressed as a % of average daily volume. Represented as a percentage.

field.name: ExchangeForPhysical
field.description: Indicates whether or not to exchange for phsyical.

field.name: OutMainCntryUIndex
field.description: Value of stocks in Currency

field.name: CrossPercent
field.description: Percentage of program that crosses in Currency. Represented as a percentage.

field.name: ProgRptReqs
field.description: Code to identify the desired frequency of progress reports.

field.name: ProgPeriodInterval
field.description: Time in minutes between each ListStatus report sent by SellSide. Zero means don't send status.

field.name: IncTaxInd
field.description: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross.

field.name: NumBidders
field.description: Indicates the total number of bidders on the list

field.name: BidTradeType
field.description: Code to represent the type of trade. (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was named "TradeType")

field.name: BasisPxType
field.description: Code to represent the basis price type.

field.name: NoBidComponents
field.description: Indicates the number of list entries.

field.name: Country
field.description: ISO Country Code in field

field.name: TotNoStrikes
field.description: Total number of strike price entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoStrikes (428) in each message that has repeating strike price entries related to the same ListID (66). Used to support fragmentation.

field.name: PriceType
field.description: Code to represent the price type. (For Financing transactions PriceType implies the "repo type" - Fixed or Floating - 9 (Yield) or 6 (Spread) respectively - and Price (44) gives the corresponding "repo rate". See Volume : "Glossary" for further value definitions)

field.name: DayOrderQty
field.description: For GT orders, the OrderQty (38) less all quantity (adjusted for stock splits) that traded on previous days. DayOrderQty (424) = OrderQty - (CumQty (14) - DayCumQty (425))

field.name: DayCumQty
field.description: Quantity on a GT order that has traded today.

field.name: DayAvgPx
field.description: The average price for quantity on a GT order that has traded today.

field.name: GTBookingInst
field.description: Code to identify whether to book out executions on a part-filled GT order on the day of execution or to accumulate.

field.name: NoStrikes
field.description: Number of list strike price entries.

field.name: ListStatusType
field.description: Code to represent the status type.

field.name: NetGrossInd
field.description: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross.

field.name: ListOrderStatus
field.description: Code to represent the status of a list order.

field.name: ExpireDate
field.description: Date of order expiration (last day the order can trade), always expressed in terms of the local market date. The time at which the order expires is determined by the local market's business practices

field.name: ListExecInstType
field.description: Identifies the type of ListExecInst (69).

field.name: CxlRejResponseTo
field.description: Identifies the type of request that a Cancel Reject is in response to.

field.name: UnderlyingCouponRate
field.description: Underlying security's CouponRate. See CouponRate (223) field for description

field.name: UnderlyingContractMultiplier
field.description: Underlying security's ContractMultiplier. See ContractMultiplier (231) field for description

field.name: ContraTradeQty
field.description: Quantity traded with the ContraBroker (375).

field.name: ContraTradeTime
field.description: Identifes the time of the trade with the ContraBroker (375). (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

field.name: LiquidityNumSecurities
field.description: Number of Securites between LiquidityPctLow (402) and LiquidityPctHigh (403) in Currency.

field.name: MultiLegReportingType
field.description: Used to indicate what an Execution Report represents (e.g. used with multi-leg securities, such as option strategies, spreads, etc.).

field.name: StrikeTime
field.description: The time at which current market prices are used to determine the value of a basket.

field.name: ListStatusText
field.description: Free format text string related to List Status.

field.name: EncodedListStatusTextLen
field.description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedListStatusText (446) field.

field.name: EncodedListStatusText
field.description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ListStatusText (444) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ListStatusText field.

field.name: PartyIDSource
field.description: Identifies class or source of the PartyID (448) value. Required if PartyID is specified. Note: applicable values depend upon PartyRole (452) specified. See "Appendix 6-G - Use of <Parties> Component Block"

field.name: PartyID
field.description: Party identifier/code. See PartyIDSource (447) and PartyRole (452). See "Appendix 6-G - Use of <Parties> Component Block"

field.name: NetChgPrevDay
field.description: Net change from previous day's closing price vs. last traded price.

field.name: PartyRole
field.description: Identifies the type or role of the PartyID (448) specified. See "Appendix 6-G - Use of <Parties> Component Block" (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

field.name: NoPartyIDs
field.description: Number of PartyID (448), PartyIDSource (447), and PartyRole (452) entries

field.name: NoSecurityAltID
field.description: Number of SecurityAltID (455) entries.

field.name: SecurityAltID
field.description: Alternate Security identifier value for this security of SecurityAltIDSource (456) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires SecurityAltIDSource.

field.name: SecurityAltIDSource
field.description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityAltID (455) value. Required if SecurityAltID is specified. Valid values: Same valid values as the SecurityIDSource (22) field

field.name: NoUnderlyingSecurityAltID
field.description: Number of UnderlyingSecurityAltID (458) entries.

field.name: UnderlyingSecurityAltID
field.description: Alternate Security identifier value for this underlying security of UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource (459) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource.

field.name: UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource
field.description: Identifies class or source of the UnderlyingSecurityAltID (458) value. Required if UnderlyingSecurityAltID is specified. Valid values: Same valid values as the SecurityIDSource (22) field

field.name: Product
field.description: Indicates the type of product the security is associated with. See also the CFICode (461) and SecurityType (167) fields.

field.name: CFICode
field.description: Indicates the type of security using ISO 10962 standard, Classification of Financial Instruments (CFI code) values. ISO 10962 is maintained by ANNA (Association of National Numbering Agencies) acting as Registration Authority. See "Appendix 6-B FIX Fields Based Upon Other Standards". See also the Product (460) and SecurityType (167) fields. It is recommended that CFICode be used instead of SecurityType (167) for non-Fixed Income instruments. A subset of possible values applicable to FIX usage are identified in "Appendix 6-D CFICode Usage - ISO 10962 Classification of Financial Instruments (CFI code)"

field.name: UnderlyingProduct
field.description: Underlying security's Product. Valid values: see Product(460) field

field.name: UnderlyingCFICode
field.description: Underlying security's CFICode. Valid values: see CFICode (461) field

field.name: TestMessageIndicator
field.description: Indicates whether or not this FIX Session is a "test" vs. "production" connection. Useful for preventing "accidents".

field.name: BookingRefID
field.description: Common reference passed to a post-trade booking process (e.g. industry matching utility).

field.name: IndividualAllocID
field.description: Unique identifier for a specific NoAllocs (78) repeating group instance (e.g. for an AllocAccount).

field.name: RoundingDirection
field.description: Specifies which direction to round For CIV - indicates whether or not the quantity of shares/units is to be rounded and in which direction where CashOrdQty (152) or (for CIV only) OrderPercent (516) are specified on an order. The default is for rounding to be at the discretion of the executing broker or fund manager. e.g. for an order specifying CashOrdQty or OrderPercent if the calculated number of shares/units was 325.76 and RoundingModulus (469) was 0 - "round down" would give 320 units, 1 - "round up" would give 330 units and "round to nearest" would give 320 units.

field.name: RoundingModulus
field.description: For CIV - a float value indicating the value to which rounding is required. i.e. 0 means round to a multiple of 0 units/shares; 0.5 means round to a multiple of 0.5 units/shares. The default, if RoundingDirection (468) is specified without RoundingModulus, is to round to a whole unit/share.

field.name: CountryOfIssue
field.description: ISO Country code of instrument issue (e.g. the country portion typically used in ISIN). Can be used in conjunction with non-ISIN SecurityID (48) (e.g. CUSIP for Municipal Bonds without ISIN) to provide uniqueness.

field.name: StateOrProvinceOfIssue
field.description: A two-character state or province abbreviation.

field.name: LocaleOfIssue
field.description: Identifies the locale. For Municipal Security Issuers other than state or province. Refer to http://www.atmos.albany.edu/cgi/stagrep-cgi Reference the IATA city codes for values. Note IATA (International Air Transport Association) maintains the codes at www.iata.org.

field.name: NoRegistDtls
field.description: The number of registration details on a Registration Instructions message

field.name: MailingDtls
field.description: Set of Correspondence address details, possibly including phone, fax, etc.

field.name: InvestorCountryOfResidence
field.description: The ISO 366 Country code (2 character) identifying which country the beneficial investor is resident for tax purposes.

field.name: PaymentRef
field.description: "Settlement Payment Reference" - A free format Payment reference to assist with reconciliation, e.g. a Client and/or Order ID number.

field.name: DistribPaymentMethod
field.description: A code identifying the payment method for a (fractional) distribution. 13 through 998 are reserved for future use Values above 1000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

field.name: CashDistribCurr
field.description: Specifies currency to be used for Cash Distributions see "Appendix 6-A Valid Currency Codes".

field.name: CommCurrency
field.description: Specifies currency to be use for Commission (12) if the Commission currency is different from the Deal Currency - see "Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes".

field.name: CancellationRights
field.description: For CIV - A one character code identifying whether Cancellation rights/Cooling off period applies.

field.name: MoneyLaunderingStatus
field.description: A one character code identifying Money laundering status.

field.name: MailingInst
field.description: Free format text to specify mailing instruction requirements, e.g. "no third party mailings".

field.name: TransBkdTime
field.description: For CIV A date and time stamp to indicate the time a CIV order was booked by the fund manager. For derivatives a date and time stamp to indicate when this order was booked with the agent prior to submission to the VMU. Indicates the time at which the order was finalized between the buyer and seller prior to submission.

field.name: ExecPriceType
field.description: For CIV - Identifies how the execution price LastPx (31) was calculated from the fund unit/share price(s) calculated at the fund valuation point.

field.name: ExecPriceAdjustment
field.description: For CIV the amount or percentage by which the fund unit/share price was adjusted, as indicated by ExecPriceType (484)

field.name: DateOfBirth
field.description: The date of birth applicable to the individual, e.g. required to open some types of tax-exempt account.

field.name: TradeReportTransType
field.description: Identifies Trade Report message transaction type (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was of type char)

field.name: CardHolderName
field.description: The name of the payment card holder as specified on the card being used for payment.

field.name: CardNumber
field.description: The number of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment.

field.name: CardExpDate
field.description: The expiry date of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment.

field.name: CardIssNum
field.description: The issue number of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment. This is only applicable to certain types of card.

field.name: PaymentMethod
field.description: A code identifying the Settlement payment method. 16 through 998 are reserved for future use Values above 1000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

field.name: RegistAcctType
field.description: For CIV - a fund manager-defined code identifying which of the fund manager's account types is required.

field.name: Designation
field.description: Free format text defining the designation to be associated with a holding on the register. Used to identify assets of a specific underlying investor using a common registration, e.g. a broker's nominee or street name.

field.name: TaxAdvantageType
field.description: For CIV - a code identifying the type of tax exempt account in which purchased shares/units are to be held. 30 - 998 are reserved for future use by recognized taxation authorities 999=Other values above 1000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

field.name: RegistRejReasonText
field.description: Text indicating reason(s) why a Registration Instruction has been rejected.

field.name: FundRenewWaiv
field.description: A one character code identifying whether the Fund based renewal commission is to be waived.

field.name: CashDistribAgentName
field.description: Name of local agent bank if for cash distributions

field.name: CashDistribAgentCode
field.description: BIC (Bank Identification Code--Swift managed) code of agent bank for cash distributions

field.name: CashDistribAgentAcctNumber
field.description: Account number at agent bank for distributions.

field.name: CashDistribPayRef
field.description: Free format Payment reference to assist with reconciliation of distributions.

field.name: CashDistribAgentAcctName
field.description: Name of account at agent bank for distributions.

field.name: CardStartDate
field.description: The start date of the card as specified on the card being used for payment.

field.name: PaymentDate
field.description: The date written on a cheque or date payment should be submitted to the relevant clearing system.

field.name: PaymentRemitterID
field.description: Identifies sender of a payment, e.g. the payment remitter or a customer reference number.

field.name: RegistStatus
field.description: Registration status as returned by the broker or (for CIV) the fund manager:

field.name: RegistRejReasonCode
field.description: Reason(s) why Registration Instructions has been rejected. The reason may be further amplified in the RegistRejReasonCode field. Possible values of reason code include:

field.name: RegistRefID
field.description: Reference identifier for the RegistID (53) with Cancel and Replace RegistTransType (54) transaction types.

field.name: RegistDtls
field.description: Set of Registration name and address details, possibly including phone, fax etc.

field.name: NoDistribInsts
field.description: The number of Distribution Instructions on a Registration Instructions message

field.name: RegistEmail
field.description: Email address relating to Registration name and address details

field.name: DistribPercentage
field.description: The amount of each distribution to go to this beneficiary, expressed as a percentage

field.name: RegistID
field.description: Unique identifier of the registration details as assigned by institution or intermediary.

field.name: RegistTransType
field.description: Identifies Registration Instructions transaction type

field.name: ExecValuationPoint
field.description: For CIV - a date and time stamp to indicate the fund valuation point with respect to which a order was priced by the fund manager.

field.name: OrderPercent
field.description: For CIV specifies the approximate order quantity desired. For a CIV Sale it specifies percentage of investor's total holding to be sold. For a CIV switch/exchange it specifies percentage of investor's cash realised from sales to be re-invested. The executing broker, intermediary or fund manager is responsible for converting and calculating OrderQty (38) in shares/units for subsequent messages.

field.name: OwnershipType
field.description: The relationship between Registration parties.

field.name: NoContAmts
field.description: The number of Contract Amount details on an Execution Report message

field.name: ContAmtType
field.description: Type of ContAmtValue (520). NOTE That Commission Amount / % in Contract Amounts is the commission actually charged, rather than the commission instructions given in Fields 2/3.

field.name: ContAmtValue
field.description: Value of Contract Amount, e.g. a financial amount or percentage as indicated by ContAmtType (519).

field.name: ContAmtCurr
field.description: Specifies currency for the Contract amount if different from the Deal Currency - see "Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes".

field.name: OwnerType
field.description: Identifies the type of owner.

field.name: PartySubID
field.description: Sub-identifier (e.g. Clearing Account for PartyRole (452)=Clearing Firm, Locate ID # for PartyRole=Locate/Lending Firm, etc). Not required when using PartyID (448), PartyIDSource (447), and PartyRole.

field.name: NestedPartyID
field.description: PartyID value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyID (448)

field.name: NestedPartyIDSource
field.description: PartyIDSource value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

field.name: SecondaryClOrdID
field.description: Assigned by the party which originates the order. Can be used to provide the ClOrdID (11) used by an exchange or executing system.

field.name: SecondaryExecID
field.description: Assigned by the party which accepts the order. Can be used to provide the ExecID (17) used by an exchange or executing system.

field.name: OrderCapacity
field.description: Designates the capacity of the firm placing the order. (as of FIX 4.3, this field replaced Rule80A (tag 47) --used in conjunction with OrderRestrictions (529) field) (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

field.name: OrderRestrictions
field.description: Restrictions associated with an order. If more than one restriction is applicable to an order, this field can contain multiple instructions separated by space.

field.name: MassCancelRequestType
field.description: Specifies scope of Order Mass Cancel Request.

field.name: MassCancelResponse
field.description: Specifies the action taken by counterparty order handling system as a result of the Order Mass Cancel Request

field.name: MassCancelRejectReason
field.description: Reason Order Mass Cancel Request was rejected

field.name: TotalAffectedOrders
field.description: Total number of orders affected by mass cancel request.

field.name: NoAffectedOrders
field.description: Number of affected orders in the repeating group of order ids.

field.name: AffectedOrderID
field.description: OrderID (37) of an order affected by a mass cancel request.

field.name: AffectedSecondaryOrderID
field.description: SecondaryOrderID (198) of an order affected by a mass cancel request.

field.name: QuoteType
field.description: Identifies the type of quote. An indicative quote is used to inform a counterparty of a market. An indicative quote does not result directly in a trade. A tradeable quote is submitted to a market and will result directly in a trade against other orders and quotes in a market. A restricted tradeable quote is submitted to a market and within a certain restriction (possibly based upon price or quantity) will automatically trade against orders. Order that do not comply with restrictions are sent to the quote issuer who can choose to accept or decline the order. A counter quote is used in the negotiation model. See Volume 7 - Product: Fixed Income for example usage.

field.name: NestedPartyRole
field.description: PartyRole value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyRole (452)

field.name: NoNestedPartyIDs
field.description: Number of NestedPartyID (524), NestedPartyIDSource (525), and NestedPartyRole (538) entries

field.name: TotalAccruedInterestAmt
field.description: Total Amount of Accrued Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income

field.name: MaturityDate
field.description: Date of maturity.

field.name: UnderlyingMaturityDate
field.description: Underlying security's maturity date. See MaturityDate (541) field for description

field.name: InstrRegistry
field.description: Values may include BIC for the depository or custodian who maintain ownership records, the ISO country code for the location of the record, or the value "ZZ" to specify physical ownership of the security (e.g. stock certificate).

field.name: CashMargin
field.description: Identifies whether an order is a margin order or a non-margin order. This is primarily used when sending orders to Japanese exchanges to indicate sell margin or buy to cover. The same tag could be assigned also by buy-side to indicate the intent to sell or buy margin and the sell-side to accept or reject (base on some validation criteria) the margin request.

field.name: NestedPartySubID
field.description: PartySubID value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartySubID (523)

field.name: Scope
field.description: Specifies the market scope of the a market data.

field.name: MDImplicitDelete
field.description: Defines how a server handles distribution of a truncated book. Defaults to broker option.

field.name: CrossID
field.description: Identifier for a cross order. Must be unique during a given trading day. Recommend that firms use the order date as part of the CrossID for Good Till Cancel (GT) orders.

field.name: CrossType
field.description: Type of cross being submitted to a market

field.name: CrossPrioritization
field.description: Indicates if one side or the other of a cross order should be prioritized. The definition of prioritization is left to the market. In some markets prioritization means which side of the cross order is applied to the market first. In other markets - prioritization may mean that the prioritized side is fully executed (sometimes referred to as the side being protected).

field.name: OrigCrossID
field.description: CrossID of the previous cross order (NOT the initial cross order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous cross order in Cross Cancel and Cross Cancel/Replace Requests.

field.name: NoSides
field.description: Number of Side repeating group instances.

field.name: Username
field.description: Userid or username.

field.name: Password
field.description: Password or passphrase.

field.name: NoLegs
field.description: Number of InstrumentLeg repeating group instances.

field.name: LegCurrency
field.description: Currency associated with a particular Leg's quantity

field.name: TotNoSecurityTypes
field.description: Indicates total number of security types in the event that multiple Security Type messages are used to return results (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was named TotalNumSecurityTypes)

field.name: NoSecurityTypes
field.description: Number of Security Type repeating group instances.

field.name: SecurityListRequestType
field.description: Identifies the type/criteria of Security List Request

field.name: SecurityRequestResult
field.description: The results returned to a Security Request message

field.name: RoundLot
field.description: The trading lot size of a security

field.name: MinTradeVol
field.description: The minimum trading volume for a security

field.name: MultiLegRptTypeReq
field.description: Indicates the method of execution reporting requested by issuer of the order.

field.name: LegPositionEffect
field.description: PositionEffect for leg of a multileg See PositionEffect (77) field for description

field.name: LegCoveredOrUncovered
field.description: CoveredOrUncovered for leg of a multileg See CoveredOrUncovered (203) field for description

field.name: LegPrice
field.description: Price for leg of a multileg See Price (44) field for description

field.name: TradSesStatusRejReason
field.description: Indicates the reason a Trading Session Status Request was rejected.

field.name: TradeRequestID
field.description: Trade Capture Report Request ID

field.name: TradeRequestType
field.description: Type of Trade Capture Report.

field.name: PreviouslyReported
field.description: Indicates if the trade capture report was previously reported to the counterparty

field.name: TradeReportID
field.description: Unique identifier of trade capture report

field.name: TradeReportRefID
field.description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE transaction types.

field.name: MatchStatus
field.description: The status of this trade with respect to matching or comparison.

field.name: MatchType
field.description: The point in the matching process at which this trade was matched.

field.name: OddLot
field.description: This trade is to be treated as an odd lot If this field is not specified, the default will be "N"

field.name: NoClearingInstructions
field.description: Number of clearing instructions

field.name: ClearingInstruction
field.description: Eligibility of this trade for clearing and central counterparty processing values above 4000 are reserved for agreement between parties

field.name: TradeInputSource
field.description: Type of input device or system from which the trade was entered.

field.name: TradeInputDevice
field.description: Specific device number, terminal number or station where trade was entered

field.name: NoDates
field.description: Number of Date fields provided in date range

field.name: AccountType
field.description: Type of account associated with an order

field.name: CustOrderCapacity
field.description: Capacity of customer placing the order Primarily used by futures exchanges to indicate the CTICode (customer type indicator) as required by the US CFTC (Commodity Futures Trading Commission).

field.name: ClOrdLinkID

field.description: The unit of measure of the underlying commodity upon which the contract is based. Two groups of units of measure enumerations are supported. Fixed Magnitude UOMs are primarily used in energy derivatives and specify a magnitude (such as, MM, Kilo, M, etc.) and the dimension (such as, watt hours, BTU's) to produce standard fixed measures (such as MWh - Megawatt-hours, MMBtu - One million BTUs). The second group, Variable Quantity UOMs, specifies the dimension as a single unit without a magnitude (or more accurately a magnitude of one) and uses the UnitOfMeasureQty(1147) field to define the quantity of units per contract. Variable Quantity UOMs are used for both commodities (such as lbs of lean cattle, bushels of corn, ounces of gold) and financial futures. Examples: For lean cattle futures contracts, a UnitOfMeasure of 'lbs' with a UnitOfMeasureQty(1147) of 40,000, means each lean cattle futures contract represents 40,000 lbs of lean cattle. For Eurodollars futures contracts, a UnitOfMeasure of USD with a UnitOfMeasureQty(1147) of 1,000,000, means a Eurodollar futures contract represents 1,000,000 USD. For gold futures contracts, a UnitOfMeasure is oz_tr (Troy ounce) with a UnitOfMeasureQty(1147) of 1,000, means each gold futures contract represents 1,000 troy ounces of gold.

field.name: AllocPositionEffect
field.description: Indicates whether the resulting position after a trade should be an opening position or closing position. Used for omnibus accounting - where accounts are held on a gross basis instead of being netted together.

field.name: DealingCapacity
field.description: Identifies role of dealer; Agent, Principal, RisklessPrincipal

field.name: InstrmtAssignmentMethod
field.description: Method under which assignment was conducted

field.name: InstrumentPartyIDSource
field.description: PartyIDSource value within an instrument partyrepeating group. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

field.name: InstrumentPartyRole
field.description: PartyRole value within an instrument partyepeating group. Same values as PartyRole (452)

field.name: NoInstrumentPartySubIDs
field.description: Number of InstrumentPartySubID (1053) and InstrumentPartySubIDType (1054) entries

field.name: InstrumentPartySubID
field.description: PartySubID value within an instrument party repeating group. Same values as PartySubID (523)

field.name: InstrumentPartySubIDType
field.description: Type of InstrumentPartySubID (1053) value. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

field.name: PositionCurrency
field.description: The Currency in which the position Amount is denominated

field.name: CalculatedCcyLastQty
field.description: Used for the calculated quantity of the other side of the currency trade. Can be derived from LastQty and LastPx.

field.name: AggressorIndicator
field.description: Used to identify whether the order initiator is an aggressor or not in the trade.

field.name: NoUndlyInstrumentParties
field.description: Identifies the number of parties identified with an underlying instrument

field.name: UndlyInstrumentPartyID
field.description: PartyID value within an underlying instrument party repeating group. Same values as PartyID (448)

field.name: UndlyInstrumentPartyIDSource
field.description: PartyIDSource value within an underlying instrument partyrepeating group. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

field.name: UndlyInstrumentPartyRole
field.description: PartyRole value within an underlying instrument partyepeating group. Same values as PartyRole (452)

field.name: NoUndlyInstrumentPartySubIDs
field.description: Number of Underlying InstrumentPartySubID (1053) and InstrumentPartySubIDType (1054) entries

field.name: UndlyInstrumentPartySubID
field.description: PartySubID value within an underlying instrument party repeating group. Same values as PartySubID (523)

field.name: UndlyInstrumentPartySubIDType
field.description: Type of underlying InstrumentPartySubID (1053) value. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

field.name: BidSwapPoints
field.description: The bid FX Swap points for an FX Swap. It is the "far bid forward points - near offer forward point". Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

field.name: OfferSwapPoints
field.description: The offer FX Swap points for an FX Swap. It is the "far offer forward points - near bid forward points". Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

field.name: LegBidForwardPoints
field.description: The bid FX forward points for the leg of an FX Swap. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

field.name: LegOfferForwardPoints
field.description: The offer FX forward points for the leg of an FX Swap. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

field.name: SwapPoints
field.description: For FX Swap, this is used to express the differential between the far leg's bid/offer and the near leg's bid/offer. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

field.name: MDQuoteType
field.description: Identifies market data quote type.

field.name: LastSwapPoints
field.description: For FX Swap, this is used to express the last market event for the differential between the far leg's bid/offer and the near leg's bid/offer in a fill or partial fill. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

field.name: SideGrossTradeAmt
field.description: The gross trade amount for this side of the trade. See also GrossTradeAmt (381) for additional definition.

field.name: LegLastForwardPoints
field.description: The forward points for this leg's fill event. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

field.name: LegCalculatedCcyLastQty
field.description: Used for the calculated quantity of the other side of the currency for this leg. Can be derived from LegQty and LegLastPx.

field.name: LegGrossTradeAmt
field.description: The gross trade amount of the leg. For FX Futures this is used to express the notional value of a fill when LegLastQty and other quantity fields are express in terms of contract size.

field.name: MaturityTime
field.description: Time of security's maturity expressed in local time with offset to UTC specified

field.name: RefOrderID
field.description: The ID reference to the order being hit or taken

field.name: RefOrderIDSource
field.description: Used to specify what identifier, provided in order depth market data, to use when hitting (taking) a specific order.

field.name: SecondaryDisplayQty
field.description: Used for reserve orders when DisplayQty applies to the primary execution market (e.g.an ECN) and another quantity is to be shown at other markets (e.g. the exchange). On orders specifies the qty to be displayed, on execution reports the currently displayed quantity.

field.name: DisplayWhen
field.description: Instructs when to refresh DisplayQty (1138).

field.name: DisplayMethod
field.description: Defines what value to use in DisplayQty (1138). If not specified the default DisplayMethod is "1"

field.name: DisplayLowQty
field.description: Defines the lower quantity limit to a randomized refresh of DisplayQty.

field.name: DisplayHighQty
field.description: Defines the upper quantity limit to a randomized refresh of DisplayQty.

field.name: DisplayMinIncr
field.description: Defines the minimum increment to be used when calculating a random refresh of DisplayQty. A user specifies this when he wants a larger increment than the standard provided by the market (e.g. the round lot size).

field.name: RefreshQty
field.description: Defines the quantity used to refresh DisplayQty.

field.name: MatchIncrement
field.description: Allows orders to specify a minimum quantity that applies to every execution (one execution could be for multiple counter-orders). The order may still fill against smaller orders, but the cumulative quantity of the execution must be in multiples of the MatchIncrement.

field.name: MaxPriceLevels
field.description: Allows an order to specify a maximum number of price levels to trade through. Only valid for aggressive orders and during continuous (autoexecution) trading sessions. Property lost when order is put on book. A partially filled order is assigned last trade price as limit price. Non-filled order behaves as ordinary Market or Limit.

field.name: PreTradeAnonymity
field.description: Allows trader to explicitly request anonymity or disclosure in pre-trade market data feeds. Anonymity is relevant in markets where counterparties are regularly disclosed in order depth feeds. Disclosure is relevant when counterparties are not normally visible.

field.name: PriceProtectionScope
field.description: Defines the type of price protection the customer requires on their order.

field.name: LotType
field.description: Defines the lot type assigned to the order.

field.name: PegPriceType
field.description: Defines the type of peg.

field.name: PeggedRefPrice
field.description: The value of the reference price that the order is pegged to. PeggedRefPrice + PegOffsetValue (211) = PeggedPrice (839) unless the limit price (44, Price) is breached. The values may not be exact due to rounding.

field.name: PegSecurityIDSource
field.description: Defines the identity of the security off whose prices the order will peg. Same values as SecurityIDSource (22)

field.name: PegSecurityID
field.description: Defines the identity of the security off whose prices the order will peg.

field.name: PegSymbol
field.description: Defines the common, 'human understood' representation of the security off whose prices the order will Peg.

field.name: PegSecurityDesc
field.description: Security description of the security off whose prices the order will Peg.

field.name: TriggerType
field.description: Defines when the trigger will hit, i.e. the action specified by the trigger instructions will come into effect.

field.name: TriggerAction
field.description: Defines the type of action to take when the trigger hits.

field.name: TriggerPrice
field.description: The price at which the trigger should hit.

field.name: TriggerSymbol
field.description: Defines the common, 'human understood' representation of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic.

field.name: TriggerSecurityID
field.description: Defines the identity of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic.

field.name: TriggerSecurityIDSource
field.description: Defines the identity of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic. Same values as SecurityIDSource (22).

field.name: TriggerSecurityDesc
field.description: Defines the security description of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic.

field.name: TriggerPriceType
field.description: The type of price that the trigger is compared to.

field.name: TriggerPriceTypeScope
field.description: Defines the type of price protection the customer requires on their order.

field.name: TriggerPriceDirection
field.description: The side from which the trigger price is reached.

field.name: TriggerNewPrice
field.description: The Price that the order should have after the trigger has hit. Could be applicable for any trigger type, but must be specified for Trigger Type 1.

field.name: TriggerOrderType
field.description: The OrdType the order should have after the trigger has hit. Required to express orders that change from Limit to Market. Other values from OrdType (40) may be used if appropriate and bilaterally agreed upon.

field.name: TriggerNewQty
field.description: The Quantity the order should have after the trigger has hit.

field.name: TriggerTradingSessionID
field.description: Defines the trading session at which the order will be activated.

field.name: TriggerTradingSessionSubID
field.description: Defines the subordinate trading session at which the order will be activated.

field.name: OrderCategory
field.description: Defines the type of interest behind a trade (fill or partial fill).

field.name: NoRootPartyIDs
field.description: Number of RootPartyID (1117), RootPartyIDSource (1118), and RootPartyRole (1119) entries

field.name: RootPartyID
field.description: PartyID value within a root parties component. Same values as PartyID (448)

field.name: RootPartyIDSource
field.description: PartyIDSource value within a root parties component. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

field.name: RootPartyRole
field.description: PartyRole value within a root parties component. Same values as PartyRole (452)

field.name: NoRootPartySubIDs
field.description: Number of RootPartySubID (1121) and RootPartySubIDType (1122) entries

field.name: RootPartySubID
field.description: PartySubID value within a root parties component. Same values as PartySubID (523)

field.name: RootPartySubIDType
field.description: Type of RootPartySubID (1121) value. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

field.name: TradeHandlingInstr
field.description: Specified how the Trade Capture Report should be handled by the Respondent.

field.name: OrigTradeHandlingInstr
field.description: Optionally used with TradeHandlingInstr = 0 to relay the trade handling instruction used when reporting the trade to the marketplace. Same values as TradeHandlingInstr (1123)

field.name: OrigTradeDate
field.description: Used to preserve original trade date when original trade is being referenced in a subsequent trade transaction such as a transfer

field.name: OrigTradeID
field.description: Used to preserve original trade id when original trade is being referenced in a subsequent trade transaction such as a transfer

field.name: OrigSecondaryTradeID
field.description: Used to preserve original secondary trade id when original trade is being referenced in a subsequent trade transaction such as a transfer

field.name: ApplVerID
field.description: Specifies the service pack release being applied at message level. Enumerated field with values assigned at time of service pack release

field.name: CstmApplVerID
field.description: Specifies a custom extension to a message being applied at the message level. Enumerated field

field.name: RefApplVerID
field.description: Specifies the service pack release being applied to a message at the session level. Enumerated field with values assigned at time of service pack release. Uses same values as ApplVerID

field.name: RefCstmApplVerID
field.description: Specifies a custom extension to a message being applied at the session level.

field.name: TZTransactTime
field.description: Transact time in the local date-time stamp with a TZ offset to UTC identified

field.name: ExDestinationIDSource
field.description: The ID source of ExDestination

field.name: ReportedPxDiff
field.description: Indicates that the reported price that is different from the market price. The price difference should be stated by using field 828 TrdType and, if required, field 829 TrdSubType

field.name: RptSys
field.description: Indicates the system or medium on which the report has been published

field.name: AllocClearingFeeIndicator
field.description: ClearingFeeIndicator(635) for Allocation, see ClearingFeeIndicator(635) for permitted values.

field.name: DefaultApplVerID
field.description: Specifies the service pack release being applied, by default, to message at the session level. Enumerated field with values assigned at time of service pack release. Uses same values as ApplVerID

field.name: DisplayQty
field.description: The quantity to be displayed . Required for reserve orders. On orders specifies the qty to be displayed, on execution reports the currently displayed quantity.

field.name: ExchangeSpecialInstructions
field.description: Free format test string related to exchange.

field.name: UnderlyingMaturityTime
field.description: Time of security's maturity expressed in local time with offset to UTC specified

field.name: LegMaturityTime
field.description: Time of security's maturity expressed in local time with offset to UTC specified

field.name: MaxTradeVol
field.description: The maximum order quantity that can be submitted for a security.

field.name: NoMDFeedTypes
field.description: The number of feed types and corresponding book depths associated with a security

field.name: MatchAlgorithm
field.description: The types of algorithm used to match orders in a specific security. Possilbe value types are FIFO, Allocation, Pro-rata, Lead Market Maker, Currency Calender.

field.name: MaxPriceVariation
field.description: The maximum price variation of an execution from one event to the next for a given security.

field.name: ImpliedMarketIndicator
field.description: Indicates that an implied market should be created for either the legs of a multi-leg instrument (Implied-in) or for the multi-leg instrument based on the existence of the legs (Implied-out). Determination as to whether implied markets should be created is generally done at the level of the multi-leg instrument. Commonly used in listed derivatives.

field.name: EventTime
field.description: Specific time of event. To be used in combination with EventDate [866]

field.name: MinPriceIncrementAmount
field.description: Minimum price increment amount associated with the MinPriceIncrement ( tag 969). For listed derivatives, the value can be calculated by multiplying MinPriceIncrement by ContractValueFactor(231).

field.name: UnitOfMeasureQty
field.description: Used to indicate the quantity of the underlying commodity unit of measure on which the contract is based, such as, 2500 lbs of lean cattle, 1000 barrels of crude oil, 1000 bushels of corn, etc. UnitOfMeasureQty is required for UnitOfMeasure(996) Variable Quantity UOMs enumerations. Refer to the definition of UnitOfMeasure(996) for more information on the use of UnitOfMeasureQty.

field.name: LowLimitPrice
field.description: Allowable low limit price for the trading day. A key parameter in validating order price. Used as the lower band for validating order prices. Orders submitted with prices below the lower limit will be rejected

field.name: HighLimitPrice
field.description: Allowable high limit price for the trading day. A key parameter in validating order price. Used as the upper band for validating order prices. Orders submitted with prices above the upper limit will be rejected

field.name: TradingReferencePrice
field.description: Reference price for the current trading price range usually representing the mid price between the HighLimitPrice and LowLimitPrice. The value may be the settlement price or closing price of the prior trading day.

field.name: SecurityGroup
field.description: An exchange specific name assigned to a group of related securities which may be concurrently affected by market events and actions.

field.name: LegNumber
field.description: Allow sequencing of Legs for a Strategy to be captured

field.name: SettlementCycleNo
field.description: Settlement cycle in which the settlement obligation was generated

field.name: SideCurrency
field.description: Used to identify the trading currency on the Trade Capture Report Side

field.name: SideSettlCurrency
field.description: Used to identify the settlement currency on the Trade Capture Report Side

field.name: CcyAmt
field.description: Net flow of Currency 1

field.name: NoSettlDetails
field.description: Used to group Each Settlement Party

field.name: SettlObligMode
field.description: Used to identify the reporting mode of the settlement obligation which is either preliminary or final

field.name: SettlObligMsgID
field.description: Message identifier for Settlement Obligation Report

field.name: SettlObligID
field.description: Unique ID for this settlement instruction.

field.name: SettlObligTransType
field.description: Transaction Type - required except where SettlInstMode is 5=Reject SSI request

field.name: SettlObligRefID
field.description: Required where SettlInstTransType is Cancel or Replace

field.name: SettlObligSource
field.description: Used to identify whether these delivery instructions are for the buyside or the sellside.

field.name: NoSettlOblig
field.description: Number of settlement obligations

field.name: QuoteMsgID
field.description: Unique identifier for a quote message.

field.name: QuoteEntryStatus
field.description: Identifies the status of an individual quote. See also QuoteStatus(297) which used for single Quotes.

field.name: TotNoCxldQuotes
field.description: Specifies the number of canceled quotes

field.name: TotNoAccQuotes
field.description: Specifies the number of accepted quotes

field.name: TotNoRejQuotes
field.description: Specifies the number of rejected quotes

field.name: PrivateQuote
field.description: Specifies whether a quote is public, i.e. available to the market, or private, i.e. available to a specified counterparty only.

field.name: RespondentType
field.description: Specifies the type of respondents requested.

field.name: MDSubBookType
field.description: Describes a class of sub book, e.g. for the separation of various lot types. The Sub Book Type indicates that the following Market Data Entries belong to a non-integrated Sub Book. Whenever provided the Sub Book must be used together with MDPriceLevel and MDEntryPositionNo in order to sort the order properly. Values are bilaterally agreed.

field.name: SecurityTradingEvent
field.description: Identifies an event related to a SecurityTradingStatus(326). An event occurs and is gone, it is not a state that applies for a period of time.

field.name: NoStatsIndicators
field.description: Number of statistics indicator repeating group entries

field.name: StatsType
field.description: Type of statistics

field.name: NoOfSecSizes
field.description: The number of secondary sizes specifies in this entry

field.name: MDSecSizeType
field.description: Specifies the type of secondary size.

field.name: MDSecSize
field.description: A part of the MDEntrySize(271) that represents secondary interest as specified by MDSecSizeType(1178).

field.name: ApplID
field.description: Identifies the application with which a message is associated. Used only if application sequencing is in effect.

field.name: ApplSeqNum
field.description: Data sequence number to be used when FIX session is not in effect

field.name: ApplBegSeqNum
field.description: Beginning range of application sequence numbers

field.name: ApplEndSeqNum
field.description: Ending range of application sequence numbers

field.name: SecurityXMLLen
field.description: Lenght of the SecurityXML data block.

field.name: SecurityXML
field.description: Actual XML data stream describing a security, normally FpML.

field.name: SecurityXMLSchema
field.description: The schema used to validate the contents of SecurityXML

field.name: RefreshIndicator
field.description: Set by the sender to tell the receiver to perform an immediate refresh of the book due to disruptions in the accompanying real-time feed 'Y' - Mandatory refresh by all participants 'N' - Process as required

field.name: Volatility
field.description: Annualized volatility for option model calculations

field.name: TimeToExpiration
field.description: Time to expiration in years calculated as the number of days remaining to expiration divided by 365 days per year.

field.name: RiskFreeRate
field.description: Interest rate. Usually some form of short term rate.

field.name: PriceUnitOfMeasure
field.description: Used to express the UOM of the price if different from the contract. In futures, this can be different for cross-rate products in which the price is quoted in units differently from the contract

field.name: PriceUnitOfMeasureQty
field.description: Used to express the UOM Quantity of the price if different from the contract. In futures, this can be different for physically delivered products in which price is quoted in a unit size different from the contract, i.e. a Cattle Future contract has a UOMQty of 40,000 and a PriceUOMQty of 100.

field.name: SettlMethod
field.description: Settlement method for a contract. Can be used as an alternative to CFI Code value

field.name: ExerciseStyle
field.description: Type of exercise of a derivatives security

field.name: UnderlyingExerciseStyle
field.description: Type of exercise of a derivatives security

field.name: LegExerciseStyle
field.description: Type of exercise of a derivatives security

field.name: OptPayAmount
field.description: Cash amount indicating the pay out associated with an option. For binary options this is a fixed amount

field.name: PriceQuoteMethod
field.description: Method for price quotation

field.name: FuturesValuationMethod
field.description: For futures, indicates type of valuation method applied

field.name: ListMethod
field.description: Indicates whether instruments are pre-listed only or can also be defined via user request

field.name: CapPrice
field.description: Used to express the ceiling price of a capped call

field.name: FloorPrice
field.description: Used to express the floor price of a capped put

field.name: NoStrikeRules
field.description: Number of strike rule entries. This block specifies the rules for determining how new strikes should be listed within the stated price range of the underlying instrument

field.name: StartStrikePxRange
field.description: Starting price for the range to which the StrikeIncrement applies. Price refers to the price of the underlying

field.name: EndStrikePxRange
field.description: Ending price of the range to which the StrikeIncrement applies. Price refers to the price of the underlying

field.name: StrikeIncrement
field.description: Value by which strike price should be incremented within the specified price range.

field.name: NoTickRules
field.description: Number of tick rules. This block specifies the rules for determining how a security ticks, i.e. the price increments at which it can be quoted and traded, depending on the current price of the security

field.name: StartTickPriceRange
field.description: Starting price range for specified tick increment

field.name: EndTickPriceRange
field.description: Ending price range for the specified tick increment

field.name: TickIncrement
field.description: Tick increment for stated price range. Specifies the valid price increments at which a security can be quoted and traded

field.name: TickRuleType
field.description: Specifies the type of tick rule which is being described

field.name: NestedInstrAttribType
field.description: Code to represent the type of instrument attribute

field.name: NestedInstrAttribValue
field.description: Attribute value appropriate to the NestedInstrAttribType field

field.name: DerivativeSymbol
field.description: Refer to definition for Symbol(55)

field.name: DerivativeSymbolSfx
field.description: Refer to definition for SymbolSfx(65)

field.description: Refer to definition for SecurityID(48)

field.description: Refer to definition for SecurityIDSoruce(22)

field.description: Refer to definition for NoSecurityAltID(454)

field.name: DerivativeSecurityAltID
field.description: Refer to definition for SecurityAltID(455)

field.description: Refer to definition for SecurityAltIDSource(456)

field.description: Refer to definition of LowLimitPrice(1148)

field.name: SecondaryHighLimitPrice
field.description: Refer to definition of HighLimitPrice(1149)

field.name: MaturityRuleID
field.description: Allows maturity rule to be referenced via an identifier so that rules do not need to be explicitly enumerated

field.name: StrikeRuleID
field.description: Allows strike rule to be referenced via an identifier so that rules do not need to be explicitly enumerated

field.name: DerivativeOptPayAmount
field.description: Cash amount indicating the pay out associated with an option. For binary options this is a fixed amount

field.name: EndMaturityMonthYear
field.description: Ending maturity month year for an option class

field.name: ProductComplex
field.description: Identifies an entire suite of products for a given market. In Futures this may be "interest rates", "agricultural", "equity indexes", etc.

field.name: DerivativeProductComplex
field.description: Refer to ProductComplex(1227)

field.name: MaturityMonthYearIncrement
field.description: Increment between successive maturities for an option class

field.name: MinLotSize
field.description: Minimum lot size allowed based on lot type specified in LotType(1093)

field.name: NoExecInstRules
field.description: Number of execution instructions

field.name: NoLotTypeRules
field.description: Number of Lot Type Rules

field.name: NoMatchRules
field.description: Number of Match Rules

field.name: NoMaturityRules
field.description: Number of maturity rules in MarurityRules component block

field.name: NoOrdTypeRules
field.description: Number of order types

field.name: NoTimeInForceRules
field.description: Number of time in force techniques

field.name: SecondaryTradingReferencePrice
field.description: Refer to definition for TradingReferencePrice(1150)

field.name: StartMaturityMonthYear
field.description: Starting maturity month year for an option class

field.name: FlexProductEligibilityIndicator
field.description: Used to indicate if a product or group of product supports the creation of flexible securities

field.name: DerivFlexProductEligibilityIndicator
field.description: Refer to FlexProductEligibilityIndicator(1242)

field.name: FlexibleIndicator
field.description: Used to indicate a derivatives security that can be defined using flexible terms. The terms commonly permitted to be defined by market participants are expiration date and strike price. FlexibleIndicator is an alternative CFICode(461) Standard/Non-standard attribute.

field.name: TradingCurrency
field.description: Used when the trading currency can differ from the price currency

field.name: DerivativeSecurityXMLLen
field.description: Refer to definition SecurityXMLLen(1184)

field.name: DerivativeSecurityXML
field.description: Refer to definition of SecurityXML(1185)

field.name: DerivativeSecurityXMLSchema
field.description: Refer to definition of SecurityXMLSchema(1186)

field.description: Refer to definition of NoParties(453)

field.description: Refer to definition of PartyID(448)

field.name: DerivativeInstrumentPartyIDSource
field.description: Refer to definition of PartyIDSource(447)

field.name: DerivativeInstrumentPartyRole

field.description: Refer to definition for NoPartySubIDs(802)

field.name: DerivativeInstrumentPartySubID
field.description: Refer to definition for PartySubID(523)

field.name: DerivativeInstrumentPartySubIDType
field.description: Refer to definition for PartySubIDType(803)

field.name: DerivativeExerciseStyle
field.description: Type of exercise of a derivatives security

field.name: MarketSegmentID
field.description: Identifies the market segment

field.name: MarketID
field.description: Identifies the Market

field.name: MaturityMonthYearIncrementUnits
field.description: Unit of measure for the Maturity Month Year Increment

field.name: MaturityMonthYearFormat
field.description: Format used to generate the MaturityMonthYear for each option

field.name: StrikeExerciseStyle
field.description: Expiration Style for an option class:

field.description: Describes the how the price limits are expressed

field.name: PriceLimitType
field.description: Describes the how the price limits are expressed

field.name: ExecInstValue
field.description: Indicates execution instructions that are valid for the specified market segment

field.name: NoTradingSessionRules
field.description: Allows trading rules to be expressed by trading session

field.name: NoMarketSegments
field.description: Number of Market Segments on which a security may trade.

field.description: Refer to definition of InstrAttribType(871)

field.description: Refer to definition of InstrAttribValue(872)

field.description: Refer to definition of PriceQuoteMethod(1196)

field.description: Refer to definition of FuturesValuationMethod(1197)

field.name: DerivativeListMethod
field.description: Indicates whether instruments are pre-listed only or can also be defined via user request

field.name: DerivativeCapPrice
field.description: Refer to definition of CapPrice(1199)

field.name: DerivativeFloorPrice
field.description: Refer to definition of FloorPrice(1200)
